<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">
Pronotum less expanded on apical portion, slightly transverse, PW/PL = 1.05, widest at about front fourth, lateral margins less bisinuate before hind angles than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[793,908,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua">
<emphasis box="[793,908,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, hind angles also rectangular, front as wide as base; disc moderately convex, sparsely pubescent; basal foveae large and deep, basal transversal impressions wellmarked. Scutellum smaller than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma, 2020" authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[543,656,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[543,656,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[664,726,261,287]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[664,726,261,287]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">
Elytra more elongated, amygdaloid, base more rounded, and apex narrower than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[1140,1253,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua">
<emphasis box="[1140,1253,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. EL/(HLm+PL) = 1.23–1.27; EL/EW = 1.64–1.68, widest at about 3/7 of elytra from base, shoulders markedly rounded, lateral margins more expanded than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[474,589,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua">
<emphasis box="[474,589,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, ciliate throughout instead of at basal half; discal surface strongly convex, pubescent; striae less evanescent than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[601,713,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua">
<emphasis box="[601,713,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; anterior discal pores of stria 3 backwardly shifted, at about basal fourth of elytra; only pore 2 of marginal umbilicate series close to marginal gutter, middle group (pores 5 and 6) widely spaced (
<figureCitation box="[326,414,477,503]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[151,192,2000,2024]" captionTargetBox="[275,1311,635,1967]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[273,1313,633,1975]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 4 Elytral chaetotaxy of Miaotrechus mahua n. sp. (A) and M. heweii n. sp. (B)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765747/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">
Legs slightly slenderer than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[546,659,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua">
<emphasis box="[546,659,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; protibia without longitudinal sulcus; tarsomere 1 much shorter than, as long as, and longer than 2–4 combined in fore, middle and hind legs respectively.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[373,441,585,611]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[151,192,1759,1783]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,786,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1435,777,1733]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 9 Male genitalia of Miaotrechus heweii n. sp. A. median lobe and parameres, lateral view; B. apical lobe of median lobe, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765757" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765757/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
): The median lobe of aedeagus much longer than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[1018,1130,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua">
<emphasis box="[1018,1130,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, strongly arcuate at median portion, apical portion largely bent ventrally and thinner; base large, sagittal aileron quite large and hyaline, inner sac armed with a short spooned copulatory piece, which is only fourth as long as aedeagus; in dorsal view, apical lobe gradually narrowed towards apex which is broader than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[874,988,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua">
<emphasis box="[874,988,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; parameres thin, each bearing only two long setae at apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765757" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3765757" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765757/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" startId="9.[151,192,1759,1783]" targetBox="[162,1425,786,1727]" targetPageId="9">
