<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="585" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1865,2036]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,152,467]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="585" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1865,1891]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma, 2020" authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[322,432,1865,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heweii" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[322,432,1865,1891]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">M. heweii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[440,502,1865,1891]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[440,502,1865,1891]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from the nominate species 
<taxonomicName authority="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma, 2020" authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[891,1005,1865,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[891,1005,1865,1891]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1012,1075,1865,1891]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1012,1075,1865,1891]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in many aspects: (1) Body thinner and wholly pubescent, 
<emphasis box="[457,488,1902,1927]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">vs.</emphasis>
stout and glabrous in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[742,857,1901,1927]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua">
<emphasis box="[742,857,1901,1927]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; (2) Antennae longer, extending at apical fourth of elytra, 
<emphasis box="[230,260,1938,1963]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">vs.</emphasis>
at apical third in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[461,575,1937,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua">
<emphasis box="[461,575,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; (3) Lateral margins of elytra ciliated throughout, middle group of marginal umbilicate series widely spaced, 
<emphasis box="[532,562,1974,1999]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">vs.</emphasis>
ciliated only on basal half, and middle group of marginal umbilicate series closely spaced in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[351,465,2009,2035]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua">
<emphasis box="[351,465,2009,2035]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; (4) Hind tarsomere 1 more elongated, longer than tarsomeres 2–4 combined, 
<emphasis box="[1349,1379,2010,2035]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">vs.</emphasis>
hind tarsomere 1 as long as tarsomeres 2–4 combined in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[719,831,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="585" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua">
<emphasis box="[719,831,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="585">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; (5) protibia not sulcate, whereas sulcate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[1316,1428,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="585" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua">
<emphasis box="[1316,1428,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="585">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and (6) Median lobe of aedeagus strongly arcuate, each paramere with two long apical setae, 
<emphasis box="[1186,1217,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="585">vs.</emphasis>
median lobe nearly straight, only slightly arcuate near apex, and each paramere with 3 or 4 long apical setae in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tian &amp; Chen &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2020" box="[1175,1288,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Miaotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="585" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahua">
<emphasis box="[1175,1288,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="585">M. mahua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="585" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,152,467]" pageId="10" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,261,287]" pageId="10" pageNumber="585">Etymology.</emphasis>
In honor of Prof. Wei He (Institute of Mountain Resources, 
<collectingRegion box="[1022,1118,261,287]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="10" pageNumber="585">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
Academy of Sciences, Guiyang), a well-known speleologist in 
<collectingCountry box="[559,630,297,323]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="585">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1095,332,360]" pageId="10" pageNumber="585" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,152,467]" box="[199,1095,332,360]" pageId="10" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,332,359]" pageId="10" pageNumber="585">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[359,455,333,359]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="10" pageNumber="585">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
(Danzhai). Known only from cave Jingua Dong (
<figureCitation box="[1012,1078,333,359]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="1.[151,192,1957,1981]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,1349,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1437,1348,1931]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIG. 1 Distribution of the genus Miaotrechus n. gen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765741/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="585">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="585" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,152,467]" pageId="10" pageNumber="585">
Jingua Dong is a small but very beautiful cave which still retains natural conditions though it has been built by the local villagers for touristic purpose. All the specimens were collected in a small wet area under decayed wood debris inside the large chamber (
<figureCitation box="[516,652,441,467]" captionStart-0="FIG" captionStart-1="FIG" captionStartId-0="10.[151,192,1391,1415]" captionStartId-1="11.[151,192,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1435,489,1365]" captionTargetBox-1="[159,1431,189,1777]" captionTargetId-0="figure@10.[151,1435,489,1365]" captionTargetId-1="figure@11.[151,1435,181,1785]" captionTargetPageId-0="10" captionTargetPageId-1="11" captionText-0="FIG. 10 Simplified map of Jingua Dong (courtesy of Wei He), the locality of Miaotrechus heweii n. sp., arrowhead showing the place where the type specimens were discovered." captionText-1="FIG. 11 Cave Jingua Dong. A-C. beauties inside cave; D. an individual of Miaotrechus heweii n. sp." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765759" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765761" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3765759/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3765761/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="585">Figs. 10–11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
